    <h1>About AP Blogs</h1>
    <h3>Welcome to AP Blogs — a place where thoughts, experiences, and knowledge come to life through words.</h1>
    <p>AP Blogs is a simple yet powerful blogging platform built with Node.js, Express, and EJS, designed to let users create, view, and manage blog posts effortlessly. Whether you're a developer experimenting with backend technologies or a writer wanting a minimal space to share your voice, this platform has you covered.</p>

    <h1>Features</h1>
    <ul>
        <li> Create and publish blog posts with ease</li>
        <li> Read and explore content in a clean UI</li>
        <li> Edit or delete your posts anytime</li>
        <li> Organized content for a smooth reading experience</li>
    </ul>

    <h1>Built With</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Node.js & Express.js – Backend and server-side logic</li>
        <li>EJS – Templating engine for rendering dynamic pages</li>
        <li>HTML & CSS – For a responsive front-end design</li>
    </ul>

    <h1>Why I Built This</h1>
    <p>As a student passionate about web development and learning by building, I created AP Blogs to strengthen my backend skills and understand how full-stack applications work — from routing and templating to database interaction.</p>
    <p>This is a continuous learning project, and I plan to enhance it with features like:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>User authentication</li>
        <li>Markdown support</li>
        <li>Rich text editor</li>
        <li>Database integration (MongoDB or PostgreSQL)</li>
    </ul>

